  "text": "Information on major nutrient efficiency in triticale is limited. Phosphorus efficiency at different rates of P supply was evaluated in several wheat, rye and triticale cultivars [CITATION_1] . P utilization efficiency was calculated as the amount of dry matter produced per unit of P accumulated in shoots, corrected for seed P content. Rye and triticale cultivars were generally more efficient in taking up and utilizing P than wheat.",
